HEADWORD: Circumambulate
<hw>Cir`cum*am"bu*late</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>circumambulatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>circumambulare</ets> to walk
around; <ets>circum + ambulare</ets>. See <er>Ambulate</er>.]</ety>
<def>To walk round about.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Cir`cum*am`bu*la"tion</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

